			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				What's sort of funny is I've thought it the other way around, I thought that Rogues can't be EVIL enough. :) Maybe I'm weird. <br>  <br> Anyway, my opinion is that if you'd like to be a good rogue, then go right ahead! I made my rogue with the idea that NOBODY was going to like him, except other rogues, because I was afraid that rogues in general were too nice. So I roleplay (Read: ROLEPLAY. I won't Kill Steal or something ooc like that) a nasty mean person.   <br> That said, the flip side should also work.  If you act like a nice rogue, and a friendly one, or whatever, then people will start saying &quot;Hey, that's (insert your name here), the nice rogue!&quot; which is fine.  <br>  <br> One final note... I don't exactly think that rogues are 'evil'.  Assuming that Dark Elves are evil, then rogues just have their own code that they follow. I'm fairly sure rogues don't consider themselves evil. *shrug* Oh, well. <br>  <br>  <br> Just my 2cp <br>  <br> Ruberot - half-elven bard of the 8th song		

