			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I think I fall into the good rogue category. I'm a wood elf who just kind of fell into the profession after losing my parents. I came from an upstanding family, Father was a ranger and Mother a jewel crafting bard. I am agnostic now but was raised to follow Tunare. I'm kinda quiet about my thieving abilities; I prefer to advertise my combat skills when I seek to join a hunting party. I never steal from other people unless they're bad (ie. bad npcs). I've become the leader of a group of individuals that are primarily good known as the Stormriders of Norrath. My love for a certain half-elven ranger also makes me want to stay good and has even made me rethink my beliefs about Tunare. Most who have met me I think would say I'm good. My story of how I got started is here - <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.geocities.com/xenith_kireikawaii/xenith.html">http://www.geocities.com/xenith_kireikawaii/xenith.html</a>  <br>  <br> ooc- There are a number of us 'Riders who really enjoy roleplaying and we've had some interesting stories. We're on E'ci if you would like to have some fun with us. Feel free to visit. :) <br> Stormrider Web Page:  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.eqstormriders.tsx.org">http://www.eqstormriders.tsx.org</a>  <br> Stormrider Message Board:  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.eqstormriders2.tsx.org">http://www.eqstormriders2.tsx.org</a>  <br>  <br>  <br> 
